question.title: Hibernate and Spring with Hibernate Annotations = "Unknown Entity..."

node.contents: I have a Project with Spring and Hibernate and I want to use Hibernate Annotations (@Entitity, @MappedSuperClass) in my classes.

astNode.text: I really don't know where the problem exactly is, but I think it might be a configuration-problem.

node.contents: Use the javax.persistence.Entity annotation instead of org.hibernate.annotations.Entity. org.hibernate.annotations.Entity only provides some hibernate-specific features to an entity already annotated with javax.persistence.Entity.

astNode.text: Use the javax.persistence.Entity annotation instead of org.hibernate.annotations.Entity. org.hibernate.annotations.Entity only provides some hibernate-specific features to an entity already annotated with javax.persistence.Entity.

node.contents: If you really want to use the Hibernate @Entity annotation, use its FQN to make it clearer it's an engine-dependent annotation:

astNode.text: If you really want to use the Hibernate @Entity annotation, use its FQN to make it clearer it's an engine-dependent annotation:
